{
  "texts": [
    "Highlights and discussionCNN models have proven effective in AHR, with a primary focus on tasks like digit, character, and word recognition.",
    "For segmentation challenges, FCN, a combination of CNN and AutoEncoder, is commonly employed for its proficiency in handling the challenges of this task [11,29,30,[33][34][35][36][37].",
    "Results vary across recognition tasks, showcasing the inherent difficulty of each problem.",
    "The accuracy levels are spanning from 96 to 100% for AHDR, 82% to 100% for AHCR, and 88% to 99% for AHWR.The observed diversity in results within the literature can be attributed to various factors such as architecture, data quality, and training hyperparameters.",
    "Hyperparameter selection poses a significant challenge in training CNNs, typically performed experimentally, demanding considerable time and effort."
  ]
}